fields.description:
JIRA macros are no longer working in Confluence pages and are displaying error messages like this one:

{noformat}
Error rendering macro 'gadget' : The gadget at https://domain-name.atlassian.net/rest/gadgets/1.0/g/com.atlassian.jira.gadgets:filter-results-gadget/gadgets/filter-results-gadget.xml was not added to this Confluence instance yet.
{noformat}

*Workaround*

Please raise a support ticket at [support.atlassian.com|https://support.atlassian.com] under *OnDemand Support* to have your gadgets added back to Confluence.

[~roberto@comalatech.com] notice a change to confluence-ui-rest in OnDemand. He is working around this, so it is not an urgent issue.

It appears the REST API to support 'expanded' responses. Before 

{{/rest/ui/1.0/content/3702785}}

Used  to respond something like:

{code}
{"id":"63735303","space":[{"id":62652417,"key":"COD","name":"Canvas OnDemand"...
{code}

Now it responds something like: 
{code}
{"id":"3702785","space":{"defined":true,"empty":false},"type":{"type":"page"}
{code}

In theory {{?expand=space}} should work, but it does not.

It may also behave differently in dev vs production modes of the server (to be confirmed).

While this is a non-published REST resource, the change was unintentional. If is it possible to support the original behaviour, we should try and restore the original behaviour.

Note that this non-published REST resource will eventually be removed, as it is being superseded by the new REST API.

h4. Steps to Reproduce:

# Export a Confluence to XML, say from a Confluence 5.1. The attached backup was created from a vanilla Confluence 5.1 with the Demonstration Space.
# Import to Confluence-only OnDemand through the Confluence OnDemand site import feature.

h4. Expected Results:

Import is successful.

h4. Actual Results:

Import process halted with this error:

bq. Import failed. Check your server logs for more information. java.lang.NullPointerException

(see screenshot attached)

The logs:

